  "body": "**Is this a bug report or feature request?**\r\n* Bug Report\r\n\r\n**Deviation from expected behavior:**\r\nUpdate of osd's failed\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (minimal and precise):**\r\nUse very long hostnames:\r\nk8s-worker-50.lxdev.ka.de.${domain with 20 chars}\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n* OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release):\r\nContainer Linux by CoreOS 1745.7.0\r\n* Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`):\r\n4.14.48-coreos-r2\r\n* Cloud provider or hardware configuration:\r\nvsphere\r\n* Rook version (use `rook version` inside of a Rook Pod):\r\n0.8.0 (in upgrade)\r\n* Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`):\r\n1.10.4\r\n* Kubernetes cluster type (e.g. Tectonic, GKE, OpenShift):\r\nSelf-managed\r\n* Storage backend status (e.g. for Ceph use `ceph health` in the [Rook Ceph toolbox]\r\nHEALTH OK\r\n\r\nI'm following https://github.com/rook/rook/blob/v0.8.0/Documentation/upgrade.md and everything worked as expected to the point where i delete all osds (kubectl -n rook delete daemonset rook-ceph-osd).\r\n\r\nThe operator gives me this logs, i think it's pretty obvious whats going wrong...\r\n```\r\n2018-07-19 07:17:31.413179 I | op-osd: checking if any nodes were removed\r\n2018-07-19 07:17:31.419842 I | op-osd: processing 0 removed nodes\r\n2018-07-19 07:17:31.419865 I | op-osd: done processing removed nodes\r\n2018-07-19 07:17:31.420202 I | exec: Running command: ceph osd unset noscrub --cluster=rook --conf=/var/lib/rook/rook/rook.config --keyring=/var/lib/rook/rook/client.admin.keyring --format json --out-file /tmp/186363335\r\n2018-07-19 07:17:32.169436 I | exec: noscrub is unset\r\n2018-07-19 07:17:32.169851 I | exec: Running command: ceph osd unset nodeep-scrub --cluster=rook --conf=/var/lib/rook/rook/rook.config --keyring=/var/lib/rook/rook/client.admin.keyring --format json --out-file /tmp/431141498\r\n2018-07-19 07:17:33.222362 I | exec: nodeep-scrub is unset\r\n2018-07-19 07:17:33.223124 E | op-cluster: failed to create cluster in namespace rook. failed to start the osds. 16 failures encountered while running osds in namespace rook: failed to create provision job for node k8s-worker-23.lxdev.ka.de.${20 char long domain}. Job.batch \"rook-ceph-osd-prepare-k8s-worker-23.lxdev.ka.de.${20 char long domain}\" is invalid: spec.template.labels: Invalid value: \"rook-ceph-osd-prepare-k8s-worker-23.lxdev.ka.de.${20 char long domain}\": must be no more than 63 characters\r\nfailed to create provision job for node k8s-worker-24.lxdev.ka.de.${20 char long domain}. Job.batch \"rook-ceph-osd-prepare-k8s-worker-24.lxdev.ka.de.${20 char long domain}\" is invalid: spec.template.labels: Invalid value: \"rook-ceph-osd-prepare-k8s-worker-24.lxdev.ka.de.${20 char long domain}\": must be no more than 63 characters\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt's repeating the error for the other nodes too.\r\n\r\nMax",
